Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_macro_place_constraint(25.10)            get_macro_place_constraint(25.10)

Name
       get_macro_place_constraint  -  Gets the current value of the macro con-
       straints that are honored by the macro placer

Syntax
        get_macro_place_constraint

       [-help]

       [-cell <string>]

       [-macro_corner_keepout]

       [-power_domain_as_core]

       [[-array <array_name>] |

       [-inst <string>  -orientation ] |

       [-cell_obs ] |

       [-track_adjustment ] |

       [-max_io_pin_group_keep_out ] |

       [-forbidden_space_to_core ] |

       [-forbidden_space_to_macro ] |

       [-min_space_to_core ] |

       [-min_space_to_macro ] |

       [-parallel_run_length ] |

       [-horizontal_stacking ] |

       [-vertical_stacking ] |

       [-honor_strict_spacing_constraint ] |

       [-avoid_abut_macro_edge_with_pins ] |

       [-same_length_site ] |

       [-pg_resource_model ] |

       [-non_default ] |

       [-halo_sharing ]|

       [-parallel_run_length_for_stacking] ]

       Gets the current value of the macro constraints that are honored by the
       macro  placer.  To  define  the  constraints   of   macros,   use   the
       set_macro_place_constraint command.

       Note:  The  report  displayed  when  the  -array,  -cell/-cell_obs,  or
       -inst/-orientation parameters are used can result in long lines on  the
       screen that are supported by ellipses (...) indicating that more infor-
       mation  about  the macro constraint follows. If you want to get all the
       information     together,     Cadence     recommends     using      the
       write_macro_place_constraint command to save all the information into a
       file.

       Note:  For 3D designs in Integrity 3D-IC platform, each die carries its
       own macro place constraint information. You must switch to  a  specific
       die before invoking the get_macro_place_constraint command.

Parameters
       -array <array_name>
              Specifies the macro array name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -avoid_abut_macro_edge_with_pins
              When  specified,  it  returns  if abutting macro edges with pins
              must be avoided even if the macro distance is within the forbid-
              den space setting.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -cell_obs <string>
              When specified, it returns the cell obstruction value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -cell <string>
              Specifies constraints for all instances of the specified cells.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -forbidden_space_to_core
              When specified, it returns the forbidden space to core value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -forbidden_space_to_macro
              When specified, it returns the forbidden space to macro value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -halo_sharing
              When specified, it returns the halo sharing mode.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each get_macro_place_constraint parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man get_macro_place_constraint

       -honor_strict_spacing_constraint
              When  specified, it returns if the forbidden spacing and minimum
              spacing constraints must be honored strictly.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -horizontal_stacking
              When specified, it returns the horizontal stacking constraint.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -inst <string>
              Specifies the macros on which the constraints are set.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -macro_corner_keepout
              When specified, it returns the macro corner keepout value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -max_io_pin_group_keep_out
              When specified, it returns the max height of the I/O pin  block-
              ages.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -min_space_to_core
              When specified, it returns the minimum space to core value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -min_space_to_macro
              When specified, it returns the minimum  space to macro value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -non_default
              When  specified,  it displays the current settings which are not
              the default settings.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -orientation
              When specified, it returns the valid orientations.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -parallel_run_length
              When specified, it returns the parallel run length value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -parallel_run_length_for_stacking
              When specified, return the stacking parallel run length value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pg_resource_model
              When specified, it returns the pg resource model details.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -power_domain_as_core
              When specified, it returns the power domain as core mode.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -same_length_site
              When specified, it returns the the minimum number of  sites  be-
              tween the vertical edge of two macros.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -track_adjustment
              When specified, it returns the track adjustment value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -vertical_stacking
              When specified, it returns the vertical stacking constraint.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The following command gets the current value of the macro con-
                straints that are honored by the macro placer.:

                get_macro_place_constraint

